# Task: Test groups creation end-to-end + fix test script cleanup

## Description

Two related testing tasks combined into one job.

Part A: Test Groups Creation
---
Groups creation is 'Needs Testing' (see docs/KNOWN_ISSUES.md). Backend has group routes, existing Go tests in `internal/api/v2/groups_test.go` (8 tests), and `scripts/test-admin-panel.sh` (33 assertions) tests admin group management. But user-facing group creation hasn't been validated end-to-end.

Steps:
1. Read `internal/api/v2/groups.go` — user-facing group CRUD
2. Read `internal/api/v2/groups_test.go` — existing 8 unit tests
3. Read `scripts/test-admin-panel.sh` — existing 33 assertions for admin groups
4. Create `scripts/test-groups.sh` integration test script for USER-FACING group operations:
   - Create group as user: `POST /api/v2.1/groups/` → 201
   - List groups: `GET /api/v2.1/groups/` → includes new group
   - Get group details: `GET /api/v2.1/groups/:id/`
   - Rename group: `PUT /api/v2.1/groups/:id/`
   - Add member: `POST /api/v2.1/groups/:id/members/`
   - List members: `GET /api/v2.1/groups/:id/members/`
   - Share library to group, verify member can see it via `/api2/beshared-repos/`
   - Remove member: `DELETE /api/v2.1/groups/:id/members/:email/`
   - Delete group: `DELETE /api/v2.1/groups/:id/`
   - Minimum 15 assertions
5. Fix any bugs found
6. Update `docs/KNOWN_ISSUES.md` — change status from 'Needs Testing'

Part B: Fix Test Script Cleanup
---
Some test scripts leave test data in the database (see docs/KNOWN_ISSUES.md 'Test Scripts Don't Fully Clean Up').

Steps:
1. Read scripts that HAVE cleanup (reference patterns):
   - `scripts/test-file-operations.sh` — has trap cleanup
   - `scripts/test-permissions.sh` — has trap cleanup
2. Read scripts that NEED cleanup:
   - `scripts/test-library-settings.sh` (74 assertions, no cleanup)
   - `scripts/test-encrypted-library-security.sh` (23 assertions, no cleanup)
3. For each script missing cleanup:
   - Add `cleanup()` function that deletes all test-created libraries/groups
   - Add `trap cleanup EXIT` at the top
   - Track created resource IDs in variables
4. Add cleanup to the new `scripts/test-groups.sh` as well
5. Update `docs/KNOWN_ISSUES.md`

Expected result:
- Groups creation confirmed working with 15+ integration test assertions
- All test scripts clean up after themselves
- Running test suite multiple times doesn't accumulate stale data

